{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Text area is a UI element that allows to type, edit, or select longer blocks of textual data, such as comments, messages or descriptions;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by expanding vertically and offering more space to input text."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides a visual and interactive affordance for multiline text entry while supporting labels, placeholders, descriptions, and validation feedback."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTextArea"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Layout","level":2,"text":"Layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Text area is based on several configurable UI elements:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"label","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": It is used to describe the purpose of the text area."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In some UI contexts, especially when space is limited or when the text area is part of a compact layout, the label can be hidden."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, hiding the label should only be done if the purpose remains clear thanks to a placeholder or contextual icon"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and if the label is still accessible to screen readers."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Hiding a label is a design choice that must balance visual simplicity and clarity of intent, without compromising inclusiveness or form guidance."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"placeholder"}]},{"type":"text","text":": If the text of the text area is empty a placeholder provides a hint or guidance inside the field to suggest expected input."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Status","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Status"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Five status are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"enabled (by default)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default neutral appearance, whether empty or filled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It allows users to click, focus, and type freely without restrictions."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"error"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"code":"error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" status indicates that the user input does not meet validation rules or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expected formatting. It provides immediate visual feedback, typically through a red border,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an error icon, and a clear, accessible error message positioned below the text area. The error message replaces the helper text."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"loading","type":"text"}]},{"text":": The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"loading"},{"type":"text","text":" state indicates that the system is processing or retrieving data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"related to the text entered. A progress indicator appears to inform the user that an action is in progress."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The field remains editable while loading."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"readOnly","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": The ","type":"text"},{"code":"readOnly","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" status lets the text visible but not editable."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}]},{"text":": In ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disabled"},{"type":"text","text":" status, the field is non-interactive and grayed out to indicate it cannot be changed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note the SwiftUI "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View.disabled()"},{"type":"text","text":" is ignored."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Helpers","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Helpers"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Helper text (plain)"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": A supporting text conveys additional information about the text area,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as how it will be used. It should ideally only take up a single line, though may wrap"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to multiple lines if required, and be either persistently visible or visible only on focus."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Helper text (characters max count)"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Uses an internal message displaying the count of remaining characters depending to the given value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is a specific iOS library feature with 1.4.0","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Helper link","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": If the helper text is not sufficient, it’s possible to offer the user"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an additional help link (the link can be external or open a modal)."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default no haptics are done by the component."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However you should think about cases where you will have to make the devices vibrate."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can refer to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/design\/human-interface-guidelines\/playing-haptics","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Mandatory-field-indication","level":2,"text":"Mandatory field indication"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields are mandatory” at the top of your formular."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Do not use an asterisk at the end of each field label, nor the word “mandatory.”"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If not all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields marked with an * are mandatory” at the top of your formular."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use an asterisk (*) at the end of each mandatory field label, and ensures this is well vocalized."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"UI rendering of the asterisk must be done with "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"bold font weight"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative content color"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (red on light backgrounds)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the mention “(optional)” at the end of each optional field label. Note that this rule is not systematic, it remains an option, to be used if needed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If there is only one field in the formular, or if the mandatory nature is obvious,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"no mention is necessary since the fields are essential to the formular’s functionality."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Outlined style","anchor":"Outlined-style"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", the text area uses a subtle background fill and a bottom border only, creating a softer and more contained look."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"outlined","type":"text"}]},{"text":", the text area uses a transparent background and a visible stroke on all four sides.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This style may be appropriate for contexts where inputs need to feel lightweight and unobtrusive,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example inside a card, a dialog, or a filtering panel."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ An outlined text area","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\", text: $text, isOutlined: true)"]},{"anchor":"Rich-text","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rich text"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rich text can be used for error and helper texts."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strong text can be used sparingly to highlight key information within the content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"No other text styles should be used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Underlined text must not be applied manually (e.g. in error message), as it is commonly associated with hyperlinks and may mislead users."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The text to display and edit","    @State var text: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ Empty text and no placeholder","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\", text: $text)","","    \/\/ Empty text with placeholder","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\", text: $text, placeholder: \"Describe your issue in detail\")","","    \/\/ With a plain helper text","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\",","                 text: $text,","                 placeholder: \"Describe your issue in detail\",","                 helperText: .plain(\"Maximum 500 characters.\"))","","    \/\/ With a maximum character count — the component shows \"X characters remaining\" (bold)","    \/\/ and switches to an error style when exceeded.","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\",","                 text: $text,","                 helperText: .charactersMaxCount(500))","","    \/\/ With helper link","    @Environment(\\.openURL) private var openUrl","","    let helperLink = OUDSTextArea.Helperlink(text: \"Helper Link\") {","       openUrl.callAsFunction(url)","    }","","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\", text: $text, placeholder: \"Placeholder\", helperLink: helperLink)","","    \/\/ With error status","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\", text: $text, status: .error(message: \"This field can't be empty.\"))","","    \/\/ Outlined style","    OUDSTextArea(label: \"Comments\", text: $text, isOutlined: true)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-text-area","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Orange","level":3,"text":"Orange"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textArea_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3,"text":"Orange Compact"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textArea_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Sosh","anchor":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_textArea_Sosh","type":"image"}]},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_textArea_Wireframe","type":"image"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.2.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Version"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.4.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Since"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTextArea"}],"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"15.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS"},{"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS"},{"introducedAt":"1.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS"}],"role":"symbol","title":"OUDSTextArea","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTextArea"}],"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents12OUDSTextAreaV","symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextArea"},"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Structures","identifiers":["do